Snapchat has launched its developer platform, called Snap Kit, TechCrunch reported. Its application programming interfaces will let developers build apps that use Snap’s login, Bitmoji avatars, display public Our Stories and Snap Map content, and generate branded stickers with referral links that users can share inside Snapchat. The Snap Kit website is also focussed on privacy, highlighting the following features of the platform: Launch partners for Snap Kit include Tinder, Patreon, and Postmates.